SUMMARY:Dismantling Racism Committee Meeting
DESCRIPTION:The Dismantling Racism Committee partners with Grace AME and Christian Temple to dismantle racism in Catonsville and our region. You are invited to join in this vital work. The committee meets monthly on the first Monday evening from 7:30 p.m. to 9:00 p.m. via Zoom. Contact the church office with questions. \nThe Dismantling Racism Committee has adopted this mission statement: \nAs concerned people of faith centered in the Catonsville community\, we see the impact racism has on societal systems and how it erects barriers that divide our communities and marginalize our neighbors. We listen to and accept the truth of racism’s long-standing\, systemic impact and boldly speak that truth to the world. We educate ourselves and others by highlighting the explicit and implicit biases that keep us from seeing and acting on the racism in ourselves and society. Therefore\, we seek to promote equity\, respect\, and justice in our communities and respect everyone’s basic right to exist and thrive.
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/dismantling-racism-committee-meeting/2026-05-04/
LOCATION:Zoom Online Meeting
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://catonsvillepres.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/iftar-17-copy.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Vickie Lord":MAILTO:lord.victoria@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
